article.description:
Sam Cassell scored 32 points and Elton Brand had
19 points and 13 rebounds to lead the Clippers to a 107-96 win over the Bulls.
article.headline: Cassell, Clippers beat Bulls, end road losing streak
article.linkText: Cassell, Clippers beat Bulls, end road losing streak
article.story:
CHICAGO (AP) -- Sam Cassell showed again what a difference he has made on the Los Angeles Clippers. Cassell scored 32 points and Elton Brand had 19 points and 13 rebounds to lead the Clippers over the Chicago Bulls 107-96 on Friday night. Vladimir Radmanovic added 14 points for the Clippers, who snapped a five-game road losing streak. Cassell carried the Clippers by scoring 20 of their 24 points during a stretch in the second and third quarters. Then in the fourth quarter, Cassell helped the Clippers pull away with back-to-back jumpers. Brand attributes the Clippers' success to players like Cassell, a 13-year veteran. "The big difference this year is having veterans with Sam and Cuttino (Mobley), we've got people who have been tested," Brand said. "They've been through it. That has really changed our team. Sam is a perfect example of that and especially today." After Andres Nocioni's dunk cut the Clippers lead to 88-83 with 7:42 left in the game, Cassell came back with a jumper. He then hit a free throw after Chris Duhon's technical, and on the next possession, he hit another jumper to give the Clippers 93-83 lead with 5:31 left. Cassell scored 11 of the final 14 points for the Clippers to close out the second quarter. He made two free throws to give Los Angeles a 47-45 lead at the half. Then he scored all the points in an 8-0 to start the third quarter. "Sam really got hot and it's easy to find him when he is like that, he gets unconscious and hits big shots for us," Brand said. Kirk Hinrich led Chicago with 21 points and Luol Deng scored 17 points and had a career-high 18 rebounds. Bulls coach Scott Skiles was not happy with some of the team's starters. "Our focus early in this game was unacceptable for a game this big. Not all across the board, but a couple of our starters just weren't ready tonight," Skiles said. Ben Gordon was 4-for-14 from the floor and was having trouble covering Cassell. The Clippers had 37 free throw attempts compared to the Bulls' 16 attempts. "They were more active. They came to win. I'm not sure what we came to do," Skiles said. Cassell finished the first half with 13 points and Brand added nine points and seven rebounds for the Clippers. Deng had eight points and 10 rebounds in the half for the Bulls. After starting the game 3-for-16 from the field, the Bulls outscored the Clippers 15-5 to close out the first quarter. Duhon made a 30-footer as time expired that gave the Bulls a 22-21 lead. Corey Maggette, in his fourth game back after missing 38 games with a separated ligament in his left foot, scored 14 points in 22 minutes and had 10 rebounds. Clippers coach Mike Dunleavy is monitoring Maggette's minutes until he gets back in playing shape. "I'm not really playing significant minutes right now so I have to be patient with it. When it's time he will take the handcuffs off, so until then I will just do what I do." Brand played his first two seasons with the Bulls before being traded to the Clippers after the 2001 season for the draft rights of Tyson Chandler and Brian Skinner.

Game notes
Dunleavy won his 100th game with the Clippers. ... Duhon and Hinrich each were issued technicals for questioning officials calls on separate incidents. ... Brand only played 6 minutes in the fourth quarter. He finished the game with three blocked shots. ... Nocioni finished with 15 points and six rebounds for Chicago.
